192.body:
Use this if you already run nginx on the server. Replace step 1 (Install Caddy) onwards with: sudo apt install nginx certbot python3-certbot-nginx sudo tee /etc/nginx/sites-available/tela-hub << 'EOF'
server { listen 80; server_name myhub.example.com; location / { proxy_pass http://localhost:8080; proxy_http_version 1.1; proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade; proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade"; proxy_set_header Host $host; proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr; }
}
EOF sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/tela-hub /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx # Obtain TLS certificate (adds HTTPS config automatically)
sudo certbot --nginx -d myhub.example.com The proxy_set_header Upgrade and Connection "upgrade" lines are required; without them the WebSocket upgrade fails silently and agents cannot connect.

